Class GlimpseBaseEvent<T>

java.lang.Object
  it.cnr.isti.labse.glimpse.api.event.GlimpseBaseEvent<T>
Type Parameters:
T - The type of the data on the payload of the GlimpseBaseEvent, see method getData() and setData(Object)
All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
GlimpseBaseEventImpl
public abstract class GlimpseBaseEvent<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

The GlimpseBaseEvent is the simple event that the monitoring infrastructure
use to infer more complex events. These object must be sent from a probe
through the ESB and should contain the information about the events to monitor or
to correlate.

The variables of GlimpseBaseEvent(String, String, String, String, int, int, Long, String)
actually are structured into the Connect context, containing information
about the connector that fires the event, about it's istance and the networked system
from which the payload is generated.

Obviously, extending the GlimpseBaseEvent(String, String, String, String, int, int, Long, String) class
it's possible to add or change variables and to manages it into the CEP using a well-formed drools rule.

Author:
acalabro
